  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2025-01-16",
    "date": "2025-04-01T20:11:52Z",
    "text": "No Retaining Every Gun In a System That Restricts Your Rights Act\n\nThis bill modifies the retention requirements for firearm transaction records of federal firearms licensees (FFLs) that go out of business.\n\nCurrent law generally requires FFLs that go out of business to deliver their firearm transaction records to the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives (ATF).\n\nThis bill removes the requirement for FFLs that go out of business to deliver their firearm transaction records to the ATF. Further, the bill requires the ATF to destroy all out-of-business records it has collected from FFLs."
  },
